 to the fore. The dilemma accompanies the reception of La Boétie's Servitude volontaire between 1574 and today. Before Walter Benjamin, the lesser-known 19th-century Léon de Laborde defended the profanity of reproducing the arts. The tension around the secular pervades the case of the College de Sociologie (Paris, 1937-1939), an attempt to analyze the ideological components of fascism. The fourth lecture approaches a much-discussed contemporary phenomenon – fake news – from a long-term perspective. To what extent are some disturbing features of the world we live in the result of a long, tortuous, unpredictable trajectory?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aReligion and politicszEuropexHistoryvCase studies. 0aSecularismzEuropexHistoryvCase studies. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aColl?ge de Sociologie.  aMachiavelli.  aSecularism.  afake news.  afascism.  areligion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2023z978311079759640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789633866429?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633866429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633866429/original  a978-3-11-079759-6  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles